{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"reasoning","text":"**Investigating loading crash**\n\nI need to examine the login callback because selecting a user seems to cause a loading crash. It might be due to the app trying to load too many images, leading to memory issues. The logs indicate that memory usage is spiking before the app exits, resulting in a permanent loading screen. \n\nIt looks like the root cause might be related to memory bloat during home loading after login. I’ll need to focus on capping image sizes and downscaling them client-side to reduce memory use effectively.\n**Confirming RSS monitor code**\n\nI need to confirm where the RSS monitor code is located, possibly searching for \"RSS exceeds.\" It might be in the main monitors that handle exits. Reducing memory usage is essential, but the user is looking for one issue at a time, with the highest priority being the loading black screen.\n\nTo pinpoint the root cause, I'll review the code and logs. The `load_home_data` function loads each poster sequentially for \"My Libraries,\" which might not be too large. I should investigate if avoiding duplicate image caching could help. I'll check the code around `items_to_media_items` to see if it loads too many images, possibly leading to repeated defaults."}}
