{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_67","type":"reasoning","text":"**Resolving memory issues**\n\nI’m looking at memory logs showing OOM errors due to image decoding in the main UI thread, likely from oversized images. The user is asking about one issue at a time, so prioritizing is essential. I'll focus on fixing the black screen caused by these OOM issues. My plan is to downscale decoded images to sensible maximum dimensions and limit cache entries. I might set a dynamic limit of 1280 pixels to keep backdrop quality intact. Reducing concurrent downloads could also help, so I should check on that.\n**Implementing targeted fixes**\n\nI’m planning to modify the decode_to_slint function to resize images if the width or height exceeds 1280 pixels, using the Triangle filter for better quality. I'll also enforce a maximum pixel count, perhaps capping it at 2,000,000 pixels. After resizing, I’ll convert the images to RGBA and make sure it compiles correctly. Additionally, I’ll consider reducing the memory cache item count from 50 to 20 to help further mitigate memory issues, aiming for a targeted fix. Let’s go ahead and patch this!"}}
